768
00:55:10,933 --> 00:55:12,894
She's a good cop looking for a home,

769
00:55:13,144 --> 00:55:16,772
- and I think she'd be a natural homicide.
- Hm.

770
00:55:16,856 --> 00:55:19,066
Well, there was an opening.

771
00:55:20,234 --> 00:55:23,279
Oops. Just filled that last night.

772
00:55:23,571 --> 00:55:26,199
Another fugitive from major crimes.

773
00:55:26,282 --> 00:55:28,326
But...

774
00:55:28,409 --> 00:55:30,953
For you, major...

775
00:55:31,037 --> 00:55:33,164
Let me see who I don't love no more.

776
00:55:36,083 --> 00:55:41,088
Ok, so, if a rocket travels, say,
1,000 miles an hour,

777
00:55:41,172 --> 00:55:43,925
how far does it go in an hour?

778
00:55:45,259 --> 00:55:46,594
Darnell.

779
00:55:53,559 --> 00:55:54,559
Chiquan?

780
00:55:54,602 --> 00:55:58,439
As far as it wants.
I mean, it's a rocket ship, right?

781
00:56:02,443 --> 00:56:05,029
- Randy?
- Is this a trick question?

782
00:56:08,115 --> 00:56:09,283
1,000 miles?

783
00:56:10,326 --> 00:56:12,036
On the money.

784
00:56:12,119 --> 00:56:14,372
Oh, Mr. Prezbo, I was gonna say that.

785
00:56:19,293 --> 00:56:21,629
Go ahead, bitch.
Laugh at me now.

786
00:56:21,796 --> 00:56:23,798
Please, please, please!

787
00:56:25,967 --> 00:56:27,468
What? You want some?

788
00:56:31,639 --> 00:56:34,934
You on the fucking floor, bitch.
Laugh at me now.

789
